subSubSection.paragraph:
Mada, Buru (
3000 feet
)).

COMMENTS: The description was based on a single specimen, still the only one in collections (
Collar, 2004a: 71
), although the species was seen twice by Stresemann during his expedition to Seram (
Rothschild and Hartert, 1921: 74
).

The Pratt brothers were Felix, Charles, and either James (
Talbot, 1920: 398
) or Joseph (
Thomas, 1920: 422
), depending on whose account one reads.
